cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with particle picking in cryo-EM micrographs, which involves image processing and analysis. This is a core area of computer vision.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a fully automatic particle picking approach, which involves training a model to recognize particles. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of machine learning to automate particle picking can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence.
4. cs.GR (Graphics) - Cryo-EM involves generating 3D reconstructions from 2D projections, which can be considered as a graphics problem.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Cryo-EM involves processing and analyzing multimedia data (micrographs), which can be considered as a sub-domain of multimedia.
